- create/choose folder
- in terminal: go to folder
- initialise Git repo
> git init
- tell Git where the remote repo is (i.e., on the internet) (if remote repo doesn't exist, you need to create it)
- copy paste:
> git remote add origin git@github.com:nancypayne/repo_name.git
- if you want to change stuff... change it (e.g., update file)
- to update to origin,
> git add --all
> git commit -m "message here"
> git push --set-upstream origin master (first time)
> git push origin (every other time)

- choose folder on (e.g.) work comp
> in terminal, go to folder
> git init
> git remote add origin git@github.com:nancypayne/repo_name.git
> git pull origin master
